1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:35,000


2
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Happy New Year, Jay.

3
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,000
I feel like I'm going crazy.

4
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,000
Or am I crazy?

5
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,000
A lot has happened since I wore this uniform.

6
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Episode E!!!

7
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,000
Why did you do that, Jay-jay?

8
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
You almost got carried away!

9
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,000
You are really crazy!

10
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,000
You are weak!

11
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Later I'll go see King Asshole.

12
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,000
And after that…

13
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
I have already accepted Yuri's proposal.

14
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,000
So I shouldn't do this to Keifer.

15
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Control yourself, Jay.

16
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,000
Yes?

17
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Yes?

18
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,000
Wow!

19
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:27,000
Jay, the room looks very nice.

20
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Is this part of your New Year's resolution?

21
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Yes, Auntie. A new look for a new life.

22
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
By the way, Yuri asked for permission.

23
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,000
He said he would pick you up. He might already be downstairs.

24
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Okay, I'll go down a little bit.

25
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Okay.

26
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,000
Yuri…

27
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,000
That's right.

28
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:58,000
I'm already engaged, so I shouldn't think about Keifer anymore.

29
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,000
You can do it, Jay-jay.

30
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:16,000
Let's forget what happened on New Year's Day.

31
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,000
Good morning.

32
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Bring it to me, I'll take it.

33
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,000
No, it's okay. It's not heavy.

34
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:20,000
Why did you choose me? I can ride a bike by myself.

35
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,000
Of course - the fiance's duty.

36
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,000
Fiancee…

37
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,000
Wow, that sounds really heavy.

38
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,000
I'm not used to it.

39
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,000
Let's go.

40
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,000
No

41
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,000
She's not going with you.

42
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,000
Leave.

43
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,000
You are not the one who decides here.

44
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:45,000
Aries, it's okay. I want to talk to Yuri too.

45
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:48,000
If you had just listened to me,

46
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,000
You will not be created in the covenant.

47
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,000
Right?

48
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Engagement ceremony...

49
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,000
Preparation...

50
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,000
Let's go.

51
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,000
Are you okay?

52
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,000
You have calmed down.

53
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,000
Of course, I'm fine.

54
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,000
Have you spoken to Angelo?

55
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,000
I'm not ready to talk to him yet.

56
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,000
I'm sorry, Jay.

57
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,000
I'm not honest about my feelings for you.

58
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:55,000
But from now on, I will be more honest.

59
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,000
We are engaged.

60
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:02,000
So I should be honest with him about what happened on New Year's Day.

61
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,000
Um, I have to confess something—

62
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Is it about Keifer?

63
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,000
It's okay, Jay.

64
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,000
I don't want to hear any more.

65
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,000
I'm sorry.

66
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,000
You don't need to apologize.

67
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,000
I understand you,

68
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,000
But I will wait for you, Jay, no matter how long.

69
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,000
Until our wedding day.

70
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,000
If that's what it takes.

71
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Yuri.

72
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,000
I'm fine, Jay.

73
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,000
Don't worry.

74
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:44,000
My only wish is for you to give me a chance.

75
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,000
Please don't close your heart.

76
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,000
I hope you still choose me in the end.

77
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,000
Honestly

78
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:01,000
I don't even know how I feel about Yuri.

79
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,000
Is there a crime?

80
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:05,000
Because he was kind to me?

81
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Or is it because of my duty to my family?

82
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Whatever happens, happens.

83
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,000
Um...

84
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:18,000
How will we tell our classmates?

85
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,000
I don't think they need to know.

86
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,000
Why?

87
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,000
It would cause chaos if they found out -

88
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,000
Especially since they know Keifer has feelings for you.

89
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,000
Yes, you're right. It can cause problems.

90
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,000
Great idea.

91
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,000
There.

92
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,000
That's good.

93
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Ouch!

94
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,000
What is that for?

95
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,000
I don't want anything awkward between us, Jay.

96
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Be like Jay, every time we're together.

97
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,000
And I will do the same.

98
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,000
You are right.

99
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,000
Ouch! That really hurts!

100
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:15,000
Isn't that enough, want one on your forehead too?

101
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:17,000
Let's go. We might be late.

102
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,000
Wait, wait.

103
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,000
- What? - I forgot something.

104
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,000
What?

105
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,000
I will go ahead.

106
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,000
Can I ask for another favor?

107
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,000
What?

108
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,000
Can you stop taking me home?

109
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:40,000
Someone might, you know, notice.

110
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,000
Okay.

111
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,000
Okay.

112
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,000
Okay, Jay-jay. We'll do what's right.

113
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:19,000
You're engaged to Yuri, it's time to forget about Keif.

114
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,000
Fight!

115
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,000
S. Insults on the first day back?

116
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,000
Or do you miss my lips?

117
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,000
What? Kiefer!

118
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,000
- Stop this. - Why?

119
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:36,000
- What do you mean "why"? Keifer, please - stop what you're doing?

120
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:41,000
This! What are you doing right now? Stop flirting with me.

121
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,000
What's wrong if I flirt with you?

122
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,000
What's wrong if I flirt with the person I love?

123
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:54,000
It's wrong.

124
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
It's like I'm cheating on Yuri.

125
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,000
We are already engaged.

126
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Stay away from me.

127
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,000
Cheating?

128
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,000
We are not in a relationship.

129
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,000
So how do we trick him?

130
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:11,000
You're not cheating Yuri.

131
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,000
Because we are not in a relationship.

132
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,000
If so, leave me alone!

133
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,000
We don't have a relationship, but...

134
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,000
You are mine.

135
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,000
You know what you're crazy about.

136
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,000
Crazy for you?

137
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,000
Yes, I think so.

138
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,000
I will wait for you, Jay, no matter how long.

139
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,000
Until our wedding day.

140
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,000
Fight!

141
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,000
You will pay for this!

142
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,000
Welcome back, guys!

143
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,000
Come on, hurry up, let's play a game.

144
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Hey!

145
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,000
How was your vacation?

146
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,000
It's okay. What about you and Mika?

147
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,000
Apparently, they're out of condoms.

148
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,000
He even asked me for some. Said it wasn't enough.

149
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,000
- He asked you? - Stupid!

150
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,000
Ah!

151
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,000
Unbelievable!

152
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,000
– Ugh! - Hey!

153
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,000
You've all gone on vacation, but you're still bitter.

154
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,000
Are you -

155
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:04,000
Stop! It's the new year, have you changed?

156
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,000
- Of course, man! - That's right!

157
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,000
He gambled away all his Christmas money.

158
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,000
- Obviously. - You're really something.

159
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,000
You have no money!

160
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,000
Hey, hey! What's going on?

161
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,000
How is Grace?

162
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,000
She has a lot of passion.

163
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,000
- She is always hungry. - That's normal.

164
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,000
Just like you.

165
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,000
Oh really?

166
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Oh, oh.

167
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,000
- It's too early in the morning. - You're disturbing me earlier!

168
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,000
Hey!

169
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:32,000
Collect your donations for food.

170
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,000
Ignore? What's wrong with him?

171
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,000
Where is Ci-N?

172
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:53,000
He's not here. He's not answering my calls.

173
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:56,000
Huh? What happened to him?

174
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,000
Should I go to their house later?

175
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,000
But what if his evil brother is there?

176
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,000
Hello, brother!

177
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,000
Bad!

178
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,000
What happened to your lips?

179
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,000
Did you go into battle?

180
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:25,000
Looks like your lips have seen some action, Keif.

181
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,000
Do you want lipstick?

182
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,000
You deserve it.

183
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,000
S.

184
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Hey, what's up?

185
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:37,000
- Hey! - Hey!

186
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,000
To us, it seems like nothing has changed.

187
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,000
Hey, it didn't hit!

188
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,000
Throw it!

189
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Ah! Hehe!

190
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,000
Fight!

191
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,000
Cool with that.

192
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:15,000
But the truth is that there have already been many changes.

193
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,000
- Hey, brother. - Ah!

194
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,000
Be determined, be determined.

195
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,000
Welcome back, class!

196
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:35,000
We have already started planning your retreat.

197
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,000
Are we included in that, sir?

198
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:42,000
All students attend a retreat before graduation.

199
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Really? So we're really done with school, right?

200
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,000
What I can say is

201
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,000
There will be many activities during the break.

202
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,000
When, sir?

203
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:57,000
There is no exact date yet, but it will be sooner than the usual retreat.

204
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:00,000
It's just a little difficult because of the final exam.

205
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
What are the final exams?

206
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,000
There is a fifth exam.

207
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:10,000
And it determines whether the student passes the exam or not.

208
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,000
Huh?

209
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,000
Why is there a fifth exam?

210
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:16,000
What if the student doesn't pass the exam?

211
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Don't worry Jay, I got you.

212
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,000
You will finish your studies.

213
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,000
Food!

214
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,000
Is that all?

215
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,000
That's all we have left.

216
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,000
You haven't been able to go into the store yet.

217
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,000
-Really! -You really are!

218
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,000
Okay, okay, okay.

219
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:45,000
Wow, hurry up, it's time to go in!

220
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,000
Do you hear anything?

221
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,000
One time!

222
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,000
It's okay here.

223
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,000
- Let's break it. - Ah!

224
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,000
Plate.

225
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,000
Plate.

226
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,000
Rice.

227
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,000
More.

228
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,000
Just eat it already.

229
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:15,000
Move to one side.

230
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,000
And if I don't want to?

231
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:25,000
Do you want me to tell them what we did before New Year's Eve?

232
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,000
What do you want?

233
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,000
Nothing.

234
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,000
You just look cute when you eat.

235
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,000
Doesn't it look bad?

236
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,000
Yes! Go away!

237
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,000
Please help share.

238
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,000
Are all of those yours?

239
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,000
Is Jay in trouble?

240
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:49,000
No, he was just joking.

241
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,000
Are you sure?

242
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,000
Remember that you are mine.

243
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,000
Hey!

244
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,000
No one follows me!

245
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,000
No one follows you.

246
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,000
It's so good there!

247
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,000
Very refreshing!

248
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:37,000
I'm sure no one will bother me here.

249
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,000
Let me call you poor.

250
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,000
He won't answer.

251
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,000
Ouch!

252
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,000
Fight!

253
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Who is that?

254
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,000
Edric!

255
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,000
I thought it was someone else!

256
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,000
What are you doing here?

257
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,000
Sorry.

258
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,000
I just can't help it.

259
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,000
Are you having problems?

260
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,000
I'm angry with myself!

261
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,000
I am such a coward!

262
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,000
Why?

263
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:39,000
Unfaithful love is very difficult!

264
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,000
I can't even tell her...

265
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,000
Or show her.

266
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,000
Yes, it's really hard.

267
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,000
But at least you're sure.

268
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,000
There is only one person.

269
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:56,000
It's even harder when you're stuck between two.

270
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,000
But who is it?

271
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:10,000
Wow, she's so pretty!

272
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,000
Freya is really beautiful.

273
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:15,000
Well, what is she really like?

274
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,000
Is that Freya?

275
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,000
F-Freya is what you're talking about?

276
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:24,000
Yes.

277
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,000
Jay, it's been a long time.

278
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Wow, what a revelation.

279
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,000
But...

280
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,000
Let's keep this between us, okay?

281
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,000
Promise?

282
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,000
Don't you have any food?

283
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:52,000
Is that food?

284
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:55,000
